introduction: In this session, we will discuss graph theory as a data structure, focusing on its concepts, terminologies, and applications in software engineering. We will cover undirected and directed graphs, graph algorithms, and complete graphs.

sections.title: Section 1: Introduction to Graphs
content: Explanation of graphs as a combination of vertices and edges.
Definition of multi-graph and directed graph.
Discussion of undirected and directed graphs.
Introduction to degree of a vertex.

sections.title: Section 2: Graph Algorithms
content: Discussion of breadth-first search and depth-first search.

sections.title: Section 3: Complete Graphs
content: Explanation of complete graphs in undirected and directed form.
Discussion of complete graphs with n vertices.
Applications of complete graphs in software engineering.

sections.title: Section 4: Graph Applications in Software Engineering
content: Explanation of graph applications in software engineering.
Discussion of graph-based data structures and algorithms.
Applications of graphs in social networks and recommendation systems.

sections.title: Section 5: Summary and Conclusion
content: Recap of the main concepts and applications of graph theory.
Conclusion and final thoughts on the importance of graph theory in software engineering.
